snippet.textDisplay:
Hello doctor Mike, I want some advice as a student. Since you are a DOCTOR, that's indicative of how much you had to study or still study. And You also find time for YouTube with your hectic work schedule. Considering these similarities. I wanted to ask you for some advice.

I am preparing for a very competitive exam in my Country which also has a lot of syllabus to cover and books to read from. It takes years to successfully crack the exam. It would really help to know

1)how to manage to study so much,
2)cope with unexpected time loss, distraction, moods,
3)coping up with sacrificing other activities, hobbies and outtings etc. And still maintain peace of mind.

I usually stick to my schedule but sometimes I find myself lost in thoughts of how's life going to be cause I don't know if I'll make it through the exam or not. If I'll ever be able to do all the bucket list items I have planned to do in the future.

it usually gets triggered by seeing someone's social media post of something they did Or some video or just disappointment or worry over incomplete tasks.

I know people suggest staying away from social media or YouTube etc but I study by myself at home and I can't find other ways of recreation when bored. I do art sometimes but even that skill is rusted these days with all the overthinking.

I hope this helps to understand my situation.
